Please save the information as "cs_top10_us_2025.xlsx" file, refer to format.xlsx, please make sure the data comes from the official website of the university or an authoritative education website. Refer to the „Ääa href="/explore-programs"„ÄãExplore Graduate Programs„Ää/a„Äã page to view each program‚Äôs testing policy.„Ää/p„Äã„Ääh3 id="gre-reporting"„ÄãReporting GRE Scores„Ää/h3„Äã„Ääp„ÄãIf you are applying to a graduate program for which the GRE is required or optional, all GRE scores we receive will be made available to the admission committee.             „Ääh1 class="variant-h1"„ÄãMS Computer Science Admission Requirements„Ää/h1„Äã

    „Ää/div„Äã„Äädiv class="block block-layout-builder block-field-blocknodecoc-basic-pagefield-basic-body"„Äã
    
        
                        „Äädiv class="field field--name-field-basic-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"„Äã„Ääp„ÄãAdmission to the program is highly selective; there are many more qualified applicants than there are places in the program. The challenge for the College every year is to select a class from a highly qualified pool. The College looks for compelling reasons to admit candidates, and the statement of purpose, letters of recommendation, test scores and GPA are all reviewed carefully. Having a strong undergraduate background in computer science, including C programming, is highly recommended for applicants. The Admissions Committee welcomes additional pertinent information that will aid in making objective and informed decisions.„Ää/p„Äã

„Ääp„ÄãStudents&nbsp;are admitted to the master's program only once a year. The application deadline is Feb. 1 for admission to the following fall semester.„Ää/p„Äã

„Ääh3„ÄãApplication Requirements„Ää/h3„Äã

„Ääul„Äã
	„Ääli„ÄãCompletion of the&nbsp;„Ääa href="http://www.gradadmiss.gatech.edu/apply-now"„Äãonline application„Ää/a„Äã.„Ää/li„Äã
	„Ääli„ÄãReceipt of three recommendation letters (requested within the on-line application).„Ää/li„Äã
	„Ääli„ÄãScores from the general Graduate Record Examination (GRE) are required. Applicant scores are expected to be at least 153 in the Verbal, 155 in the Quantitative, and 3.0 in the Analytical sections for the MS program. &nbsp;This requirement cannot be waived.„Ää/li„Äã
	„Ääli„ÄãThe desirable minimum&nbsp;„Äästrong„ÄãGPA is 3.0/4.0„Ää/strong„Äã, though most candidates score higher.„Ää/li„Äã
	„Ääli„Äã„Ääa href="https://grad.gatech.edu/english-proficiency"„ÄãSee the Institute's English Proficiency Requirements.„Ää/a„Äã&nbsp; Our department requires a 100 minimum score on the TOEFL.&nbsp;We will also accept IELTS to fulfill english proficiency.&nbsp; A minimum overall score of 7.5 is required, with minimum section scores as follows:&nbsp; Reading 6.5, Listening 6.5, Speaking 6.5, Writing 5.5.„Ää/li„Äã
„Ää/ul„Äã

„Ääp„ÄãA student who is enrolled in another graduate program of the Institute may pursue an MSCS while that student is also pursuing his or her degree in the other major. To be granted permission to pursue the MSCS, a student must submit to the Office of Graduate Programs in the College of Computing the material required for admission to the MSCS program. This includes transcripts, letters of recommendation, and the GRE General Test. If the student is approved by the admissions committee to pursue the MSCS, the student will be notified in writing. At no time will a student outside the College be allowed to pursue a concurrent degree without prior permission of the admissions committee.„Ää/p„Äã

„Ääp„Äã„Ääa href="https://prod-cc.cc.gatech.edu/ms-computer-science-admissions-faq"„ÄãAdmissions FAQ„Ää/a„Äã„Ää/p„Äã„Ää/div„Äã
      
    „Ää/div„Äã
      „Ää/div„Äã
